{"type":"message","id":"e3ea9610","parentId":"114f2ff9","timestamp":"2026-03-30T09:14:14.705Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1774862053917_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Sierra Blu Realty — OpenClaw Tools Configuration\n\n## Allowed Tools\n\nThe following tools are enabled for the Sierra Blu AI concierge:\n\n### Communication\n- `whatsapp` — Send and receive WhatsApp messages\n- `telegram` — Send and receive Telegram messages\n\n### Data & Search\n- `read` — Read files from the workspace\n- `write` — Write files to the workspace\n- `bash` — Execute shell commands (sandboxed)\n- `browser` — Browse the web for property research\n\n### Automation\n- `cron` — Schedule recurring tasks (follow-ups, syncs)\n- `sessions_list` — View active conversations\n- `sessions_history` — Access conversation history\n- `sessions_send` — Send messages to active sessions\n\n## Denied Tools (Security)\n\nThe following tools are explicitly blocked for non-main sessions:\n- `gateway` — No access to gateway configuration\n- `canvas` — Not needed for real estate operations\n- `nodes` — No remote node access\n\n## Custom Scripts\n\n### Lead Export\n```bash\n# Export leads from Firestore to CSV\nnode openclaw/scripts/export-leads.js\n```\n\n### Sync Status Check\n```bash\n# Check Property Finder sync status\nnode openclaw/scripts/check-sync.js\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774862054703}}
